                <h1>PROJECTS</h1>
                <img src="cnn.jpg" alt="">
                <h2>SIGN LANGUAGE RECOGNITION USING CNN</h2>
                <p>-Sign language recognition is a crucial aspect of human-computer interaction for individuals who are deaf or hard of hearing. Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) have emerged as a promising approach for accurate sign language recognition. In this context, a CNN-based system can be designed to recognize sign language from visual data, such as images or videos, by extracting features from the input data.
                </p>
                <p>-The core idea is to feed the extracted features into a classification layer, which maps the input to a sign language vocabulary. The effectiveness of CNN-based sign language recognition systems relies on the quality of the training data, the choice of architecture, and the robustness to variations in lighting, pose, and background.  
                </p>
                <h2>MESSAGE ENCODING AND DECODING IN SECURITY ASPECTS</h2>
                <img src="ende.jpg" alt="">
                <p>
                    -In the context of security, encoding and decoding refer to techniques used to protect sensitive information from unauthorized access. Encoding involves converting plaintext data into a non-readable format, making it difficult for hackers to intercept or read. Common encoding methods include symmetric and asymmetric encryption, hashing, and encoding schemes like Base64.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                    -Decoding is the reverse process, converting the encoded data back to its original form. Effective encoding and decoding processes are crucial in cybersecurity to prevent data breaches, protect sensitive information, and ensure the integrity of digital communications.
                </p>
